flow-table-haipin
=================

*** This is work in progress ***

What is flow-table-hairpin?
---------------------------

User space daemon to use the unft driver for the Linux Kernel.
It is designed to allow Flow Table API messages to be hairpined
back to user-space thus allowing the NDOs to be backed by
an implementation in user-space.

The Flow Table API is being developed in the flow-net-next repository
https://github.com/jrfastab/flow-net-next/commits/master

What is here?
-------------

flow-table-haripind: a daemon that uses the unft driver to
implement the Flow Table API NDOs in user-space.

What other documentation is available?
--------------------------------------

None at this time

